document_data.History:
In the {{yearlinkName|1372}}, Azoun was just an orphaned babe, and Regent [[Alusair Obarskyr]] and Dowager Queen [[Filfaeril Obarskyr]] were ruling Cormyr until he came of age. Azoun was cared for by [[Alaphondar]], Royal Sage of Cormyr and lover of Filfaeril. The utmost care was given to keep Azoun's whereabouts a secret, as there were many ambitious malcontents who would wish to do him harm.{{Cite dungeon/198/Cormyr Royale: The Royal Court of the Forest Kingdom|46}}

When he finally came of age in the {{yearlinkName|1384}}, at the insistence of the royal court, he was crowned king.{{Cite dungeon/198/Cormyr Royale: The Royal Court of the Forest Kingdom|61-62}}

The [[1385 DR|following year]], Azoun had to deal with the effects of the [[Spellplague]] and the death/disappearance of a third of his elite [[War Wizards]].

He managed to fulfill his royal duties, however, and married [[Nalara Marliir]], siring two children, [[Emvar Obarskyr|Emvar]] and [[Foril I Obarskyr|Foril]] in [[1409 DR]].{{Cite dragon/365/Backdrop: Cormyr|17}} Emvar, however, was later murdered in [[1437 DR]] by [[Sembia]]ns, along with Foril's wife, [[Jemra Rhindaun|Jemra]].

Two years later, in [[1439 DR]], Cormyr entered into a two-year-long war with [[Sembia]], now a vassal state of [[Netheril]].

Finally, a peace treaty was made and [[Daerlun]] seceded from Cormyr.{{Cite dragon/365/Backdrop: Cormyr|20}} shortly before his death in the {{yearlinkName|1449}}.
